hdzero-osd-lab — attribution and provenance

This project is licensed MIT (see LICENSE). The following notes document
inspirations and cross-referenced sources. None of the referenced third-party
source code is copied into this repository; reimplementations are from public
data and documented behavior.

1. HD OSD Font Tools (Python, MIT)
   https://github.com/ondrascz/HD-OSD-Font-Tools
   The compositor logic (glyph subsets, switch/extension/offset matrix,
   logo-tile wrapping, MCM parser semantics, super-sampled TTF rendering)
   was originally authored there by ondrascz. This project's TypeScript
   compositor is a clean-room reimplementation inspired by that tool and
   by a WhiteRqbbit fork that added palette TTF rendering and per-glyph
   image overrides.

2. Betaflight Configurator (JavaScript, GPL-3.0)
   https://github.com/betaflight/betaflight-configurator
   Betaflight's OSD tab defines the element table and default layout
   positions referenced by this project's `src/osd-schema/`. We read the
   Configurator source to cross-check element names, default grid
   positions, and glyph-code assignments, but we do not copy code. Our
   schema is a newly-authored TypeScript data table, MIT-licensed.

3. HDZero Configurator (JavaScript)
   https://github.com/hd-zero/hdzero-configurator
   Referenced for HD-specific OSD element additions and the canonical
   SD-card font path `resource/OSD/FC/BTFL_000.bmp`.

4. game-icons.net (icons, CC BY 3.0)
   https://game-icons.net
   Sample decorative icons shipped with this tool are sourced from
   game-icons.net under CC BY 3.0. Individual author credits
   (e.g. Lorc, Delapouite) appear alongside each bundled asset.

5. opentype.js (MIT)
   https://github.com/opentypejs/opentype.js
   Runtime dependency for parsing TTF/OTF font files in the browser.

6. pixelmatch (ISC)
   https://github.com/mapbox/pixelmatch
   Dev-time dependency for visual regression testing.

All third-party runtime code is listed in `package.json` with its license
recorded here when added.
